03:37.787 --> 03:40.266
Karim told me everything.

03:40.267 --> 03:42.146
You've been smoking pot.

03:42.147 --> 03:43.906
And don't even try and deny it

03:43.907 --> 03:47.066
because your eyes are bloodshot to
buggery.

03:47.067 --> 03:49.826
So, what? You drink - there's no
difference.

03:49.827 --> 03:53.827
Yeah, well, there is a difference.
Pot is illegal and I'm not a child.

03:54.107 --> 03:56.546
I'M not a child. You're 16, Rae!

03:56.547 --> 03:59.626
You're not even allowed to buy
alcohol, or drive,

03:59.627 --> 04:02.666
or purchase fireworks,
or become an MP.

04:02.667 --> 04:06.466
I want you back by ten from now on.
Every night.

04:06.467 --> 04:07.986
You can't put a curfew on me.

04:07.987 --> 04:09.386
It looks like I just did.

04:09.387 --> 04:12.906
Or do not want me to buy you food
and give you lifts everywhere?

04:12.907 --> 04:16.546
You know, all the stuff you can't do
because you're not an adult.

04:16.547 --> 04:19.507
But... Conversation over.

04:21.707 --> 04:25.707
And don't expect a lift to
Chloe's party tomorrow.

04:31.627 --> 04:35.627
'I don't want a sodding lift! God, I
am sick of being treated like a kid!

04:36.187 --> 04:40.186
'I need to get out of this house.

04:40.187 --> 04:42.746
'I didn't need my mum to get by.

04:42.747 --> 04:44.626
'I'm 16, for God's sake.

04:44.627 --> 04:48.627
'All I needed was the help of an old
friend - Mr BMX Special.'

04:57.347 --> 05:01.347
'Sometimes, it's the small
things in life that feel good -

05:02.107 --> 05:05.506
'the sun on your face,
the wind in your hair...

05:05.507 --> 05:09.507
'Feels like freedom.'

05:14.747 --> 05:18.747
Argh! Bollocks!

05:27.307 --> 05:29.626
Hello. Hiya!

05:29.627 --> 05:32.626
Happy birthday. Thank you.

05:32.627 --> 05:35.986
What is it?

05:35.987 --> 05:39.426
Oh, Babe! Oh!

05:39.427 --> 05:41.786
Oh, it's like we're best mates
or something!

05:41.787 --> 05:45.787
Oh, I wouldn't go that far.
Thank you. It's lovely. Chloe?

05:45.947 --> 05:49.947
Thought maybe
you'd like your present.

05:50.467 --> 05:54.426
There you go. Be careful.
Are you ready?

05:54.427 --> 05:58.427
Go on, get on with it!

06:03.467 --> 06:06.786
Oh, my God!

06:06.787 --> 06:10.746
Oh, my God! Thank you! Thank you!

06:10.747 --> 06:12.226
'How was it that Chloe had a dad

06:12.227 --> 06:16.227
'who treated her like she wasn't
still in nappies?

06:16.787 --> 06:18.946
'And all I had was...'

06:18.947 --> 06:22.947
Whose is this bike?

06:29.627 --> 06:33.627
Simmie said something to Archie.
Something mean.

06:34.227 --> 06:37.946
Chop, you play football with them,
can't you say something? Yeah.

06:37.947 --> 06:41.947
Maybe he was just joking,
like, you know, just messing around?

06:42.147 --> 06:46.147
Forget about it. It's fine.

06:47.667 --> 06:50.746
'Oh, God. No!'

06:50.747 --> 06:54.746
You all right? Yeah.

06:54.747 --> 06:58.226
There we go. All right?
All right? Hiya.

06:58.227 --> 06:59.586
Do you want a drink, girl?

06:59.587 --> 07:01.506
'Girl? I thought I was a girl.'

07:01.507 --> 07:03.186
I'll have a Baileys and ice, please.

07:03.187 --> 07:05.146
'Look at her.

07:05.147 --> 07:06.626
'Just because she's 24,

07:06.627 --> 07:10.026
'she thinks she's more sophisticated
than the rest of us,

07:10.027 --> 07:12.866
'just because she drinks Bailey's.'

07:12.867 --> 07:15.226
Rae, do you want
another snakebite and black?

07:15.227 --> 07:18.026
Yeah. No!

07:18.027 --> 07:21.226
No, I'll have a sherry, please.

07:21.227 --> 07:23.666
A sherry? Hm. OK.

07:23.667 --> 07:27.667
So, you're Rae?
Finn has told me so much about you.

07:29.267 --> 07:33.267
Back in a sec. OK, little bug.

07:33.427 --> 07:36.826
'Little bug? What the fuck?!

07:36.827 --> 07:40.827
'I literally cannot watch this.'

07:42.747 --> 07:46.747
Oh, bollocks, I've just remembered
I've got a thing with a pigeon.

07:49.467 --> 07:53.467
I mean... race.

07:53.907 --> 07:57.907
I've got to go.

08:04.307 --> 08:07.786
'Little bug?
What does that even mean?

08:07.787 --> 08:09.906
'So what if she was 24, beautiful,

08:09.907 --> 08:12.906
had her own flat, swanky job,
her own car.

08:12.907 --> 08:14.626
'I may as well be nine years old,

08:14.627 --> 08:18.066
'sitting in a boy's bedroom
playing computer games.

08:18.067 --> 08:20.986
'I bet Olivia doesn't play
computer games.

08:20.987 --> 08:24.267
'She's far too busy being grown-up
and seducing her man.'

08:28.027 --> 08:32.027
Whoa, there! What are you doing?

08:32.746 --> 08:36.746
Did you not like it?
No, I liked it, but it's just...

08:38.386 --> 08:41.586
I don't want a girlfriend.
Maybe I don't want a boyfriend.

08:41.587 --> 08:44.746
What?

08:44.747 --> 08:47.626
Are you hinting that we should have a
casual relationship, Rae?

08:47.627 --> 08:48.906
Maybe.

08:48.907 --> 08:51.386
Do you not like me, or something?

08:51.387 --> 08:53.426
No, I like you,

08:53.427 --> 08:56.986
but you're not the type of person
to have a casual relationship.

08:56.987 --> 09:00.786
You're not ready for that.
You're too... Too what?

09:00.787 --> 09:02.466
..young.

09:02.467 --> 09:03.986
Thanks!

09:03.987 --> 09:06.986
Young in terms of experience.

09:06.987 --> 09:09.666
Great. Fine. Thanks.

09:09.667 --> 09:13.667
'Sometimes I felt like the world was
conspiring against me.'

09:13.707 --> 09:16.866
Rae?

09:16.867 --> 09:20.867
What are you doing? Nice wheels.

09:30.067 --> 09:33.026
That's when I realised that my mum
and Liam were right.

09:33.027 --> 09:37.027
I was a bloody kid...
and it had to stop.

09:40.627 --> 09:42.386
Anything pink had to go.

09:42.387 --> 09:45.106
Anything with glitter on it
had to go.

09:45.107 --> 09:49.107
Anything that resembled a Troll or
a fairy or a cartoon animal

09:49.947 --> 09:52.707
or had a heart on it, it had to go.

09:57.427 --> 10:01.306
I've been clearing out a load of old
junk to make way for my new stuff.

10:01.307 --> 10:04.186
Any complaints can be
made in writing

10:04.187 --> 10:08.187
and will be processed through the
usual channels, AKA the dustbin.

10:12.747 --> 10:15.146
'So maybe it was going to take
more than a sherry

10:15.147 --> 10:17.626
'and a bin bag full of glitter pens
and Trolls.

10:17.627 --> 10:21.186
'I needed to find another way to
show the world I WAS an adult,

10:21.187 --> 10:24.622
'to show my mum
I wasn't a kid any more.'

10:58.358 --> 11:02.358
Is that Dad?

11:04.654 --> 11:08.654
Yeah, that's your dad.

11:10.454 --> 11:13.773
Does he live local?

11:13.774 --> 11:16.533
He lives in Lincolnshire, yeah.

11:16.534 --> 11:20.333
I want his address.

11:20.334 --> 11:22.093
No.

11:22.094 --> 11:24.773
I want to write to him. No, he...

11:24.774 --> 11:27.093
Mum...

11:27.094 --> 11:31.094
..I'm 16.

11:32.574 --> 11:35.893
I'll think about it.

11:35.894 --> 11:39.894
'The funny thing was, I didn't even
know if I would write to him.

11:40.334 --> 11:44.334
'But maybe he'd treat me
like an adult.'

11:46.574 --> 11:50.574
I've, um...
I've got a scan on Monday.

11:51.174 --> 11:55.053
Karim's starting his evening shift
so he can't come.

11:55.054 --> 11:58.333
I just want someone to be there.

11:58.334 --> 12:00.693
I don't feel very well.

12:00.694 --> 12:03.213
I'm just a little bit worried.

12:03.214 --> 12:04.813
Will you come with me?

12:04.814 --> 12:06.653
Yeah.

12:06.654 --> 12:10.654
'course I will.

12:17.694 --> 12:20.293
I'm sorry, Rae, but you have
to do an assessed performance

12:20.294 --> 12:21.533
or you won't pass this year.

12:21.534 --> 12:24.573
You either involve yourself
in the choir project,

12:24.574 --> 12:26.333
or you can become a prostitute,

12:26.334 --> 12:29.053
in the boys' stage adaptation
of Scarface.

12:29.054 --> 12:31.733
It's up to you.

12:31.734 --> 12:32.933
So I think a cappella.

12:32.934 --> 12:35.173
We've still not decided what
song we're going to do.

12:35.174 --> 12:37.333
We could easily add another
part in for you. No.

12:37.334 --> 12:40.013
No, I'll just, erm,
print stuff off, make drinks...

12:40.014 --> 12:42.813
Chloe, listen to this.

12:42.814 --> 12:44.773
One, two, three...

12:44.774 --> 12:48.774
# Stay with me

12:52.054 --> 12:56.054
# Stay with me

12:56.694 --> 12:59.813
# E-e-e-e-e. #

12:59.814 --> 13:01.173
It's great.

13:01.174 --> 13:04.733
I mean, it needs a little bit
of work, but it is great, isn't it?

13:04.734 --> 13:06.933
Yeah!

13:06.934 --> 13:09.773
Oh, by the way, I'm going to West
Paddock Fair tonight with the boys,

13:09.774 --> 13:11.613
if you fancy it. "Boys"?

13:11.614 --> 13:13.613
Well...

13:13.614 --> 13:15.093
Men.

13:15.094 --> 13:16.493
No.

13:16.494 --> 13:18.933
No, I can't.
I said I'd go with the gang, so...

13:18.934 --> 13:22.934
So, I saw you with your bite
the other night and, well...

13:23.014 --> 13:24.493
Well, what?

13:24.494 --> 13:27.214
Chloe!

13:50.494 --> 13:52.733
All right, this is Ian.

13:52.734 --> 13:56.013
That's Ben, that's Joe, and this...

13:56.014 --> 14:00.014
This is Saul.

14:00.174 --> 14:03.173
You look nice.

14:03.174 --> 14:04.813
What?

14:04.814 --> 14:08.814
You look nice.

14:08.934 --> 14:12.253
Thanks. So Chloe says
that you're a big muso.

14:12.254 --> 14:14.333
What, you like Led Zep?

14:14.334 --> 14:17.693
Does the Pope shit in a hat
and punch it?

14:17.694 --> 14:19.213
He sure does.

14:19.214 --> 14:21.653
You're a pretty cool
customer, aren't you?

14:21.654 --> 14:24.333
Oh, well, it has been said before.

14:24.334 --> 14:28.334
Yeah, I like that.

14:29.174 --> 14:32.453
It doesn't hurt that you're...
very attractive.

14:32.454 --> 14:34.973
Hey, Rae, you coming?

14:34.974 --> 14:38.173
He's going to eat a kebab
and then go on a gravity wheel.

14:38.174 --> 14:41.333
Nothing's going to happen -
my guts are made of titanium.

14:41.334 --> 14:45.334
You can hang out with us,
Rae, if you want.

14:49.654 --> 14:51.533
I'll catch you guys in a bit, yeah?

14:51.534 --> 14:55.534
I'm just going to
keep an eye on Chloe.

15:27.054 --> 15:29.253
No. I'm not getting in that.

15:29.254 --> 15:33.254
Why not? He's fine...
You're fine, Ian, aren't you?

15:35.254 --> 15:37.693
I can walk you if you want, Rae.

15:37.694 --> 15:41.694
That's cool, cos that sorts out
the seating arrangements. Let's go.

15:41.974 --> 15:45.373
Chlo, what you doing?

15:45.374 --> 15:49.374
Don't sweat it.

15:49.534 --> 15:51.933
Shall we?

15:51.934 --> 15:55.934
OK.

16:02.414 --> 16:04.293
'The more pissed I got,

16:04.294 --> 16:05.453
'the more I didn't care

16:05.454 --> 16:08.293
that Saul wasn't exactly
the fittest lad in the world.

16:08.294 --> 16:10.893
'He wanted to hear
what I thought about stuff,

16:10.894 --> 16:12.133
'important stuff.'

16:12.134 --> 16:16.134
D'you smoke? Obviously.

16:17.414 --> 16:20.293
All right, what do you say
we just jump off here then?

16:20.294 --> 16:22.973
Just go to a bar or something?

16:22.974 --> 16:26.373
OK. But just one.

16:26.374 --> 16:29.533
Yeah, just a nightcap. One.

16:29.534 --> 16:33.534
One.

16:44.974 --> 16:48.093
There's something about
staying up until the sun rises

16:48.094 --> 16:49.773
and the birds start cheeping

16:49.774 --> 16:51.813
that is beyond cool.

16:51.814 --> 16:55.253
It's freedom.

16:55.254 --> 16:56.893
Especially when you get back

16:56.894 --> 16:58.973
half an hour before
your mum gets up,

16:58.974 --> 17:02.974
so she'll never find out.

17:06.493 --> 17:10.493
Ooh. Where the bloody hell
have you been?!

17:14.253 --> 17:16.373
Been out with friends.

17:16.374 --> 17:19.532
Friends?

17:19.534 --> 17:21.492
It's six o'clock in the morning.

17:21.493 --> 17:23.613
I've rung everyone.

17:23.614 --> 17:27.532
Chloe, Archie, Izzy -
I've even rung the hospital.

17:27.534 --> 17:29.973
Look, I'm sorry, all right?

17:29.974 --> 17:32.413
No, no, no, it's not
fuckin' all right!

17:32.414 --> 17:35.453
Why didn't you call me?

17:35.454 --> 17:39.454
Why do you never think
about anybody apart from yourself?

17:39.614 --> 17:42.293
Chill out.

17:42.294 --> 17:45.453
There is no need to curse at me.

17:45.454 --> 17:48.773
I've said I'm sorry. I'm 16.

17:48.774 --> 17:51.293
I can do what I want.

17:51.294 --> 17:52.773
Oh, right, yeah, yeah.

17:52.774 --> 17:55.573
You're 16, you can do what you want
now, make your own decisions,

17:55.574 --> 17:58.853
like staying out till six o'clock
on a Thursday night.

17:58.854 --> 18:00.653
Whatever.

18:00.654 --> 18:04.654
Don't "whatever" me.
Don't you EVER "whatever" me.

18:05.294 --> 18:08.693
I'm pregnant, in case
you hadn't noticed.

18:08.694 --> 18:11.173
I feel horrible!

18:11.174 --> 18:15.174
I haven't slept all night.

18:16.454 --> 18:20.454
If you want to behave like that,
feel free to move out.

18:21.814 --> 18:24.253
No, I mean it.

18:24.254 --> 18:28.254
You never know, maybe your dad'll
let you live with him.

18:29.134 --> 18:33.134
In fact, you know what...

18:40.574 --> 18:43.213
Here.

18:43.214 --> 18:47.214
You want to write to him,
write to him.

18:47.374 --> 18:50.053
Do me a favour, move in with him.

18:50.054 --> 18:52.413
I've done my shift.

18:52.414 --> 18:54.693
What did you just say to me?

18:54.694 --> 18:57.133
You heard me crystal-clear, love.

18:57.134 --> 19:00.293
I don't want my baby growing up
around someone like you.

19:00.294 --> 19:04.294
Fuck you.

19:28.334 --> 19:29.613
I knew I'd messed up,

19:29.614 --> 19:33.573
but there was no way my mum
should've spoken to me like that.

19:33.574 --> 19:36.533
I bet my dad would never
treat me like this.

19:36.534 --> 19:40.534
And it looks like I was
about to be replaced anyway.

19:47.214 --> 19:49.973
"Dear Dad..."

19:49.974 --> 19:53.293
Problem was that
I knew nothing about him.

19:53.294 --> 19:55.573
I couldn't even
imagine him reading it.

19:55.574 --> 19:57.413
"Dear Victor...

19:57.414 --> 20:01.133
"just wanted to get in touch
and say hi...

20:01.134 --> 20:05.134
"and here's my address.

20:05.174 --> 20:07.693
"Hope to hear from you.

20:07.694 --> 20:11.694
"All the best, Rae."

20:12.414 --> 20:14.573
Usually when I get
a hangover like this

20:14.574 --> 20:17.613
I get the demons
whispering into my ears,

20:17.614 --> 20:19.493
but today it was the opposite,

20:19.494 --> 20:22.813
things were more clear now
than they'd ever been.

20:22.814 --> 20:25.613
I was waiting for people
to treat me like an adult,

20:25.614 --> 20:28.734
so it was time
to make adult decisions.

20:47.454 --> 20:51.454
'This was such a bad idea.'

20:52.494 --> 20:56.494
Can I help you?

20:57.654 --> 20:59.373
I, erm...

20:59.374 --> 21:01.752
Hello.

21:03.294 --> 21:07.294
Hiya.

21:10.494 --> 21:12.140
Rachel.

21:25.814 --> 21:28.293
I like your lamp.

21:28.294 --> 21:30.053
Oh, thanks.

21:30.054 --> 21:32.253
I work in antiques.

21:32.254 --> 21:36.254
It's, erm, '20s Art Deco.

21:37.694 --> 21:41.694
Do you want to borrow anything? Oh,
I don't have a record player. What?

21:42.654 --> 21:45.053
You've got to have a record player!

21:45.054 --> 21:47.853
I mean, the sound
quality is just pfff!

21:47.854 --> 21:51.854
I'll ask for one for my birthday
but I doubt I'll get it.

21:53.294 --> 21:57.294
When... when is your birthday?

21:57.534 --> 22:01.534
Three weeks.

22:05.174 --> 22:08.733
Look, this is so, erm...

22:08.734 --> 22:12.734
I don't know, I should have
rung. Are you angry with me?

22:17.414 --> 22:20.813
Just wanted to come and see you,

22:20.814 --> 22:24.814
meet you.

22:26.494 --> 22:30.494
If you need anything, just say it.

22:31.054 --> 22:35.054
Well, you could give me a
lift home after this brew.

22:37.894 --> 22:40.973
Got a good group of friends?

22:40.974 --> 22:42.613
Yeah.

22:42.614 --> 22:44.653
The best!

22:44.654 --> 22:46.933
So, what do you get up to?

22:46.934 --> 22:50.293
Go to the pub, drive
around. What, you drive?

22:50.294 --> 22:52.493
No, I'm 16.

22:52.494 --> 22:55.493
But your birthday's coming up soon,
you want to get in lots of practice.

22:55.494 --> 22:57.493
Make sure you pass
your test first time.

